dismissalText.commentary: Suresh Raina c Bell b Woakes 83 (98b 8x4 2x6 149m) SR: 84.69

dismissalComment.html: caught at midwicket! Raina has pulled the short of length delivery straight to Bell at the edge of the circle at midwicket. It was a slower delivery and that is what put Raina off his shot probably, normally he hits them quite well. How important is that wicket for England! Raina was India's last recognised batsman.

dismissalComment.html: caught at point! Charges down the track to a flatter delivery and wanted to hit that over long-on, but there is some turn, enough for the ball to take a thick outside edge and lob to the fielder at point.

dismissalText.commentary: MS Dhoni lbw b Finn 15 (23b 2x4 0x6 38m) SR: 65.21

dismissalComment.html: Cook's plan to bring back Finn has made impact immediately. It was length ball angling in to Dhoni and the batsman had walked across, as he has been doing, to play that towards the leg side. But Finn is quick and he beats Dhoni's attempted flick, hits him in front of middle..

dismissalComment.html: oh no! Root goes for an uncharacteristic cross-batted shot and he misses. Jadeja normally keeps it a touch short of length and  Root didn't get to the pitch of the ball in his sweep, he misses and Jadeja hits off. Immediate impact.

Jadeja runs around from deep midwicket to take a good running catch close to the boundary. Big blow for England

headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: Bell takes his team home by dabbing the ball on the off side and completing a comfortable win

commentPostTextItems.html: So India take the series 3-2. It comes as a relief in a season in which they haven't really had much to cheer about. Alan Gardener's match report is being updated as i type. Thanks for all your comments and feedback. This is Devashish Fuloria signing off, ciao ciao.

Alastair Cook: "It was good win, it was a good toss to win, but our bowlers bowled really well. Bresnan and Finn got early breakthroughs today. Our top four got runs and Bell played a fantastic knock. The pitch was doing something all day, so it was important to stick around with wickets in hands, it is important with the new regulations. We have good positives to take from this series. It has been a fantastic three months in India. "

Ian Bell is the man of the match for his super century"Our bowlers set up the win but 220 odd was a good target to chase. I really love opening the batting and hopefully I can continue do this in future. "

Suresh Raina gets the Man of the Series award. "When we came to this series, we had lost to Pakistan and England in Tests, so this win has been good. Today we were probably 20-30 runs short, but still we batted well in this series. When you bat 6, 7 you don't get many opportunities, but this series, our top order didn't get runs, so I got time in the middle. "

MS Dhoni: "Series was as tight as the Test series. We should have won this game, maybe we should have batted more sensibly. But it is a young side and it will learn with time. Thankfully, in three games, we didn't have to bowl those death overs, it remains an area of concern. Today bowlers got some help, maybe there were a little short today. The bowlers did well this series because the conditions really helped them too. Ishant was a big positive, he bowled really well throughout the series, if you look spell by spell. Fielding is a big positive. Jadeja's form solves the allrounder problem to an extent too."

An utterly brilliant and well-paced century by Ian Bell takes England home comfortably with a few overs to spare. He played some effortless shots and took his time, but didn't give it away at all and made sure he finished the job. England make it 2-3 in the series and there are some smiles now that they head-off to a limited-overs tour to NZ. The win puts England level with India on the ODI ranking points at 119, but India are slightly ahead after taking the decimals into account. India kept the pressure on during the initial part of the innings but England kept building up partnerships and thwarted the home side. Morgan made a welcome return to form with an unbeaten 40 too.
Raina's Uncle: "Man of the Match should be Raina! if he hand't scored 83, Bell wouldn't have had the opportunity of scoring a 100!"
Musawwir: "@Raina's Uncle: Don't worry! That's exactly they are going to do it. Remember the previous series...?" I won't be surprised if Dhoni sweeps the MoM and MoS awards.

commentTextItems.html: easily done! fuller delivery on off stump and Bell sweetly times it through extra cover, the fielder at the deep didn't really make an effort, but a gorgeous drive nonetheless
in the channel outside off, Bell stretches forward and pushes it to deep cover for a single. He is doing it easily

commentPreTextItems.html: Sudheer: "Enough!! The contest is over here, at least for Indian supporters..lets switch to Australian Open, a final-worth-contest going on there..the final still didn't turn in favour to either of them even two-and-half sets have completed.Come on Djoko." You lucky guys.

commentTextItems.html: length ball on off stump this time, defended towards cover
slower ball on a length outside off, Bell gets beside the line and dabs it to the left of backward point
short of length on off, defended to the leg side
runs coming in thick and fast now. He gets a full delivery on the pads and beautifully drives it past a diving midwicket all the way to the boundary

commentPreTextItems.html: Paul: "Sounds like Goran was an interesting bunch of guys!"
Sharma is back into the attack

commentTextItems.html: short of length outside off, Morgan guides it to third man
fuller delivery outside off, Morgan bunts it on the pitch, the ball then bounces over the head of the bowler and they take a single
it's getting hot in here! Short ball, Morgan pulls it flat and deep into the stands at deep backward square
shuffles across and flicks the full delivery on the off and middle through square leg. There is no one at the deep, so backward square has to pull it back
short of length delivery outside off, he opens the face, but straight to point
Wallop!! fuller delivery outside off, no half-measures from him, cracks it over long-off with a full swing of the bat

commentPreTextItems.html: Damir Gubic: "No wonder you miss Goran. He said there were three of him at every match. good Goran, bad Goran and crazy Goran"

commentTextItems.html: short of length ball outside off, Bell plays a forehand down the line to long-off
attempts the sweep again, but is nowhere near the pitch of the ball, gets hit on the front pad, but outside the line of off
flighted delivery on off and middle, it is flicked through to deep midwicket
goes for the sweep, but doesn't get hold of it and almost drags it to the leg stump, the ball rolls past Dhoni and they take a single
slower delivery on the middle, defended off the front foot
on the off side, he cuts it straight to point
fuller delivery on off and middle, Morgan jabs at it with a lot of bottom-hand and it travel over long-on so easily. Beautifully timed

dismissalComment.html: caught at point! Charges down the track to a flatter delivery and wanted to hit that over long-on, but there is some turn, enough for the ball to take a thick outside edge and lob to the fielder at point.

dismissalText.commentary: Suresh Raina c Bell b Woakes 83 (98b 8x4 2x6 149m) SR: 84.69

dismissalComment.html: caught at midwicket! Raina has pulled the short of length delivery straight to Bell at the edge of the circle at midwicket. It was a slower delivery and that is what put Raina off his shot probably, normally he hits them quite well. How important is that wicket for England! Raina was India's last recognised batsman.

headshotImage.caption: Samit Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Samit Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ravichandran Ashwin c Finn b Patel 19 (21b 1x4 1x6 32m) SR: 90.47

dismissalComment.html: caught at square leg! tries to sweep again but the ball is flat and short. He ends up half-pulling, half-sweeping, the ball takes a top edge and lobs towards square leg and Finn, running around from short fine, takes an easy catch

headshotImage.caption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Bhuvneshwar Kumar c Finn b Bresnan 31 (30b 5x4 0x6 27m) SR: 103.33

dismissalComment.html: caught at mid-off! Bhuvi's little cameo comes to an end as he only manages to get a toe-end of the bat at this slower delivery outside off. Finn, at mid-off, shows how it is done by running in and diving forward to complete a good low catch

headshotImage.caption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammed Shami c & b Bresnan 1 (6b 0x4 0x6 12m) SR: 16.66

dismissalComment.html: quick bouncer gives Bresnan his fourth! It was too quick for Shami, who tries to pull the ball, but gets a top edge on to the helmet and it then just lobs up for the bowler to complete the catch

headshotImage.caption: Alastair Cook player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Alastair Cook player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Alastair Cook player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Alastair Cook player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Alastair Cook b I Sharma 22 (40b 5x4 0x6 50m) SR: 55

dismissalComment.html: he has knocked the middle stump back! It was on a good length area and cuts back into the batsman just enough. Cook was neither forward nor backward and paid the price as he missed the line of the ball to lose his middle. Ishant is pumped and Cook, for once, is not lbw.

dismissalText.commentary: Ian Bell not out 113 (143b 13x4 1x6 197m) SR: 79.02

headshotImage.longCaption: Kevin Pietersen player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Kevin Pietersen player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kevin Pietersen player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kevin Pietersen c Jadeja b Mohammed Shami 6 (12b 1x4 0x6 31m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: caught at deep midwicket! Shami attempts a short ball and it was slightly quicker too. KP instinctively went for a pul, but that bounced a touch more than he anticipated, and he doesn't get hold of that shot. Jadeja runs around from deep midwicket to take a good running catch close to the boundary. Big blow for England

dismissalText.commentary: Joe Root b Jadeja 31 (49b 4x4 0x6 64m) SR: 63.26

dismissalComment.html: oh no! Root goes for an uncharacteristic cross-batted shot and he misses. Jadeja normally keeps it a touch short of length and  Root didn't get to the pitch of the ball in his sweep, he misses and Jadeja hits off. Immediate impact.

dismissalText.commentary: Eoin Morgan not out 40 (40b 0x4 3x6 49m) SR: 100
